! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|v0.1.11 |2026-05-25 |''Constraints / options / ref-types editing in the per-field stage.'' Three array-valued field-def properties now have cascade-mode editing surfaces, each gated on the field's typed value the same way the type-builder cells are. ''constraints'' ‚Äî drill row (applicable iff typed is not `$title`/`$calculated`, via `kind.required-applicable`); picker stage has toggle rows for `required` / `unique` / `unique:wiki`. Each toggle binds `ca-bind-type: application/x-string-array` + `ca-bind-path: <idx>,constraints` + `ca-true-value: <constraint>`; cascade-palette's existing list-membership toggle semantics (`fireToggle` for STRING_ARRAY_TYPE) adds/removes the value cleanly. ''options'' ‚Äî text-edit row with `ca-bind-type: application/x-string-array` (applicable iff typed=enum), bound to `<idx>,options`. Space ‚Üí type comma-OR-space-separated values ‚Üí Enter; the scribetype's `toField` splits on whitespace and writes a real JSON array, `fromField` joins back for display. Free-form to match the type-builder's options cell. ''ref-types'' ‚Äî drill row (applicable iff typed=ref); picker has toggle rows for every existing kind (`[function[kind.types-all]get[kind.type]] +[unique[]sort[]]`). Toggle adds/removes the kind from the field's ref-types array. ''Drill row value display'' ‚Äî when the bound JSON path is an array, cascade-palette's `_renderBoundDrillValue` joins with `, ` for display (e.g. `required, unique` next to the constraints drill). Since the read at the drill level doesn't use string-array bind-type, the raw array reaches the renderer's `Array.isArray` branch ‚Äî gives a nicer comma-separated display than the space-separated form the toggle picker uses internally. ''Deferred:'' parameterised constraints (`min:N` / `max:N` / `custom`) need an extra arg input ‚Äî needs the same text-then-action wiring the create-new-kind / add-new-field flows need. New helpers: `kind.cascade-field-array-prop-row`, `kind.cascade-field-{constraints,options,reftypes}-{drill-row|picker-items}`, `kind.cascade-constraint-applicable`, `kind.cascade-array-toggle-build`. Tiddler-only ‚Äî no restart. |
|v0.1.10 |2026-05-25 |''+ Add field from library: common-fields picker in Manage-kinds.'' New leaf ''+ Add field from library‚Ä¶'' (üìö, order 700, grouped under fields) sits at the bottom of the per-kind field list. Drilling lists every common-field tiddler tagged `$:/tags/rimir/kind/common-field` ''that isn't already on this kind'' (uses `kind.is-common-field-unused` ‚Äî same filter the type-builder's library dropdown uses). Each common-field row shows ''`<key> ¬∑ <typed>`'' + the field's icon. Picking one appends its `def` JSON to `kind.fields` at the next index AND appends its key to `kind.stream-fields`, then `ca-after-fire: pop`s back to the kind-edit stage so the new field row appears immediately. ''Action wiring:'' since the per-CF leaf needs to read the picked CF's `def` field and the kind's current `kind.fields` length at fire time, the action wikitext can't be a single short `$action-setfield` ‚Äî it needs `<$let>` to compute next-idx + cf-def + cf-key first. The leaf's `ca-actions` therefore calls a new `\procedure kind.cascade-add-cf-to-kind(target-tid, cf-tid)` via `<$transclude $variable="‚Ä¶" target-tid="‚Ä¶" cf-tid="‚Ä¶"/>` with both tids baked in at item-build time. The procedure body is the existing type-builder's add-common-field logic (the `jsonset:json<idx>,<cf-def>` + `+[append<cf-key>]` listops pair) wrapped in a `<$let>`. `invokeViaNavigator` renders the action tree before invokeActions so the transcluded procedure's action widgets fire normally. ''New helpers:'' `kind.cascade-add-from-library-row` (the "+" leaf), `kind.cascade-add-from-library-items` (picker items-from), `kind.cascade-cf-leaf-build` + three sub-helpers (`-with-key`, `-with-typed`, `-with-icon`) that thread cf-key / cf-typed / cf-icon through the chain, and the `kind.cascade-add-cf-to-kind` procedure. Tiddler-only ‚Äî no restart. |
|v0.1.9 |2026-05-25 |''Typed + cardinality as drill-pickers.'' The 0.1.8 field-edit stage forced the user to type `enum` / `ref` / `$calculated` / `single` / `multi` correctly in a text input. Both are now proper drill-pickers. ''typed'' drill opens a 9-leaf picker (`text` / `longtext` / `number` / `date` / `datetime` / `enum` / `ref` / `$title` / `$calculated`); picking writes the chosen value to `kind.fields[<idx>],typed` via `<$action-setfield $tiddler=‚Ä¶ kind.fields={{{ [‚Ä¶jsonset[<idx>],[typed],[<value>]] }}}/>` and `ca-after-fire: pop`s back to the field-edit stage. ''cardinality'' drill (conditionally present per `kind.cardinality-applicable`) opens a 2-leaf picker (`single` / `multi`). Each picker drill row carries `ca-bind-tiddler`/`-field`/`-path` so cascade-palette's `_renderBoundDrillValue` surfaces the current value alongside the row ‚Äî Space ‚Üí drill ‚Üí pick ‚Üí return is the keyboard flow. ''Applicability is dynamic'' ‚Äî changing typed from `ref` to `text` makes the cardinality row disappear on next render (cascade-palette refreshes the items-from on every tiddler change), matching the type-builder UI's "disabled when text" cell. ''New helpers:'' generic `kind.cascade-field-drill-row(kind-tid, field-idx, prop, caption, icon, order, picker-fn)` builds a drill row for any prop with a configurable picker function; `kind.cascade-jsonset-leaf-build(kind-tid, field-idx, prop, value)` builds a leaf that writes one JSON-path value (shared between typed and cardinality pickers); two picker-items functions `kind.cascade-field-typed-picker-items` and `kind.cascade-field-cardinality-picker-items` emit the static enum lists. ''Still deferred:'' common-fields library picker ("+ Add field from library") ‚Äî needs procedure-as-action wiring (the per-CF leaf's actions need to read the picked CF's `def` field at fire time and append it to kind.fields, which is more wikitext than fits cleanly in a bake-time string-built ca-actions). Tiddler-only ‚Äî no restart. |
|v0.1.8 |2026-05-25 |''Per-field property editing.'' Field rows in the Manage-kinds drill (the `<key> ¬∑ <typed>` rows from 0.1.7) are now ''drill'' rows that open a per-field edit stage. The stage shows text-edit rows for ''typed'' / ''caption'' / ''icon'' (always present) and ''cardinality'' (conditionally present, only when typed is `enum` or `ref` ‚Äî uses the existing `kind.cardinality-applicable` helper that the type-builder UI already uses to disable that cell for text-typed fields). Each row is `ca-kind: text` with `ca-bind-path: <field-idx>,<prop>` walking into the `kind.fields` JSON array ‚Äî Space enters edit mode, Enter commits, value lands directly on the right JSON sub-path. A confirm-wrapped ''üóë Delete this field'' leaf at the bottom calls the existing `kind.rebuilt-fields-without` helper (the same rebuild-by-filter used by the type-builder's delete-field button ‚Äî `jsonset[N]` would corrupt the array to a sparse object per [[tw-gotchas-filters#jsonset on a JSON ARRAY converts it to an OBJECT]]). ''Same applicability rules the type-builder uses already work here'' because the cascade-mode reuses `kind.cardinality-applicable`. ''Deferred to next iteration:'' typed / cardinality as proper drill-pickers (currently plain text-edit ‚Äî user has to type `enum` correctly); constraints / options / ref-types editing (string arrays need either string-array bind-type or sub-stage pickers); ''+ Add new field'' (needs the text-then-action wiring); common-fields library picker (drill into `$:/tags/rimir/kind/common-field` and copy the picked def into kind.fields). New helpers: `kind.cascade-field-edit-items`, `kind.cascade-field-prop-row`, `kind.cascade-field-cardinality-row`, `kind.cascade-field-delete-row`. Field rows now use `ca-kind: drill` instead of `ca-kind: leaf`. Tiddler-only ‚Äî no restart. |
|v0.1.7 |2026-05-25 |''Fix: Manage-kinds metadata rows showed "(unset)" everywhere + added per-kind field-list rows.'' Two issues. ''(unset) everywhere:'' the metadata rows tried to bind via `<parent-picked>` to read each `kind.*` field, but cascade-palette's generic filter-drill does NOT propagate the picked title into the new stage's `parentPicked` ‚Äî only entity-type / action-menu drills do (see cp-firing.js:489 vs :501). So `<parent-picked>` was empty, `ca-bind-tiddler` was empty, and every row's `_readBoundRaw` returned undefined ‚Üí rendered as "(unset)". ''Fix:'' bake the kind-tid into the items-from filter string at row-build time (`"ca-items-from":"[function[kind.cascade-kind-edit-items],[<kind-tid>]]"`); the function now takes the kind-tid as an explicit parameter and threads it through every per-row helper. Same fix the existing instance-create flow already used (`kind.kind-find-build`, `kind.kind-create-build` etc.). ''Per-kind field list:'' user reported every kind showed the same 5 metadata rows even though the kinds differ (task has caption/abbrev/parent; project has just name; person is empty; etc.) ‚Äî the kind.fields JSON array wasn't surfaced. Added a row per element of `kind.fields` (name = "`<key>` ¬∑ `<typed>`", ordered first via `ca-order:<idx>`, grouped under "fields"), so drilling into "task" now shows three rows on top of the metadata rows: `caption ¬∑ text`, `abbrev ¬∑ text`, `parent ¬∑ ref`. Field rows are currently leaves with no action (editing them per-property is the next iteration); they make the per-kind variation externally legible. New helpers: `kind.cascade-kind-field-rows`, `kind.cascade-field-row`, `kind.cascade-field-row-with-key`, `kind.cascade-field-row-build`. Metadata rows moved to order 500-540 (under "metadata" group), delete leaf at 900 (under "danger" group). Tiddler-only ‚Äî no restart. |
|v0.1.6 |2026-05-25 |''Fix: Manage-kinds entry showed nothing.'' Hit the documented [[`\import` walker stops at first non-setvariable node|tw-gotchas-parser-pragma]] gotcha ‚Äî `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` opened with `\import $:/plugins/rimir/kind/engine` followed by an HTML comment block, then the `\function` definitions. The cross-tiddler macro walker (which propagates setvariable defs to importers) stops at the first non-setvariable node it encounters; `\import` is non-setvariable, so every `\function` after it silently dropped from cascade-palette's view ‚Üí the items-from filter resolved to nothing ‚Üí empty drill. ''Fix:'' rewrote the file with all `\function` declarations consecutively at the top (engine's functions are already in scope via cascade-palette's startup-time `\import [tag[$:/tags/Macro]‚Ä¶]`, so the local `\import` of engine was redundant anyway); dropped all body-level HTML comments (they're also non-setvariable nodes ‚Äî even with `\import` removed, comments interspersed between functions would have stopped the walker too). Now matches the existing `cascade-helpers.tid` layout. Tiddler-only ‚Äî no restart. |
|v0.1.5 |2026-05-25 |''Cascade-palette: Manage kinds (edit existing type-defs).'' New `palette/` subfolder ships a cascade-palette entry "Manage kinds" (`üß∞`, order 130, grouped under Kind Actions) tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`. Drilling lists every existing kind type-definition tiddler as a row (caption + icon resolved from `kind.caption` / `kind.icon`). Picking a kind drills to a metadata-edit stage with five text-edit rows ‚Äî one per flat `kind.*` field (`caption`, `icon`, `namespaces`, `title-formula`, `stream-fields`) ‚Äî bound directly to the type-def tiddler. Each row uses cascade-palette's `ca-kind: text` so Space enters edit mode, Enter commits the new value to the type-def. A confirm-wrapped ''üóë Delete this kind'' leaf at the bottom removes the type-def tiddler (instances unaffected). ''Files:'' new `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` (wikitext function library mirroring the existing cascade-helpers' addprefix/addsuffix JSON-emission pattern ‚Äî `kind.cascade-manage-kinds-items`, `kind.cascade-manage-kind-row`, `kind.cascade-kind-edit-items`, `kind.cascade-meta-row`, `kind.cascade-delete-kind-row`) and `palette/entries/manage-kinds.tid` (the root entry). Editing the per-field `kind.fields` JSON array stays in the existing type-builder tab for now ‚Äî follow-up will add cascade-mode field-list editing. Pure tiddler changes ‚Äî no JS, no restart. |
|v0.1.4 |2026-05-21 |Ships ''`scopes/instances-of.tid`'' ‚Äî a cascade-palette scope tiddler tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/scope`''. Adds the `,` prefix so the user can type `,<kind>` to restrict any cascade-palette result list to instances of that kind (e.g. `,node` filters to `[tag[node]]`). Argument is a kind tiddler title. Pure tiddler change ‚Äî no JS, no restart. Requires cascade-palette ‚â• 0.0.25 for the scope strip mechanism. |
|v0.1.3 |2026-05-21 |All three root entries (`Find entity`, `Find by kind`, `Create entity`) now carry `ca-group: Kind Actions` so they cluster under a shared header in the cascade-palette root menu (when grouping is enabled) instead of falling back to the auto-derived plugin name "kind". Tiddler-only change. |
|v0.1.2 |2026-05-21 |''Cascade integration ‚Äî drill-fixing pass.'' (a) Fixed `kind.is-editable-field` ‚Äî was `:filter[function[kind.is-computed-typed],‚Ä¶is[blank]]` which always evaluated to empty (`is[blank]` operates on titles, and is-computed-typed outputs `$title`/`$calculated` non-blank when matched), so every field was rejected as "not editable". Now uses `count[]match[0]` to keep fields where is-computed-typed produced zero rows. (b) `kind.save-leaf-build` rewritten ‚Äî earlier version closed the JSON string with `\"}` (JSON-escaped quote = quote INSIDE the string, never closing it) AND emitted filter args as `"K","D"` (quoted strings are not a valid filter operand form). Now closes with `"}` and uses literal-bracket args `[K],[D]` (with brackets injected via the `_brackets` textref to dodge the parser's bracket counter). Same `\"}`‚Üí`"}` fix on `kind.kind-find-build` / `kind.kind-create-build`. (c) `kind.collection-build` now embeds `ca-bind-tiddler` + `ca-bind-field` so cascade-palette can render the currently-selected value on the right of single/multi-select picker drills (Parent etc.) ‚Äî empty ‚Üí `(unset)`, single ref ‚Üí caption, multi ‚Üí comma-joined. (d) `kind.cascade-fields-for-create` split so `:map:flat[field-edit-items]` runs ONLY over the draft-tid, not over the save-leaf JSON (previous version mapped both, producing one empty result + skipping the actual field edits). New helper `kind.field-edit-items-for-draft`. (e) Single-select picker leaves (`kind.enum-leaf-one`, `kind.ref-leaf-build`) now emit `ca-after-fire: pop` ‚Äî cascade-palette fires the action, pops the picker stage, keeps the palette open on the create-fields stage. Pure tiddler changes ‚Äî no restart required. |
|v0.1.1 |2026-05-21 |Cascade-palette integration. Three new root entries: `Find entity` (cross-type search by caption+title), `Find by kind` (drill kinds ‚Üí instances), `Create entity` (in-palette draft + Save leaf). Three universal actions on any `kind.type`-tagged tiddler: `Open`, `Edit fields` (per-field menu with kind data-types: text/longtext/number/date/datetime/enum/ref), `Delete` (with confirm-drill). One palette template renders `view.tid` in the details drawer. All field synthesis runs through `cascade-helpers.tid` (~50 filter functions, no JS) |
|v0.1.0 |2026-05-20 |Initial release. One-tiddler-per-type schema model with namespacing; hand-rolled editor/creator/view/stream-view/validator/type-builder; field types text/longtext/number/date/datetime/enum/ref ($title and $calculated for computed values); constraints required/min/max/unique/unique:wiki; auto-computed titles via filter formula |
